      <TEXTAREA NAME="body" ROWS="15"
        COLS="50" WRAP="virtual">>I just finished this quest (finally) on 
>Bertox.  Unless you're prepared to 
>kill Lynuga, or have the money 
>to either hire someone to kill 
>her or buy the ruby, I'd 
>suggest waiting on this quest.  
>Here's how I did it tho, 
>from start to finish. 
>Go to Paw, go to the room 
>with the stream running thru it. 
> There's a hole in the 
>floor underneath the stream.  Swim 
>down there, and go thru the 
>door that leads into the larger 
>chamber.  In a small room 
>to your right, you'll see aq 
>bunch of splitpaw nobles and possibly 
>Kurrpok Splitpaw.  Kill him, get 
>ruby pendant, gate out. 
>Start a ranger character.  Get him/her 
>up to lvl4 as fast as 
>you can.  Run to WKarana. 
> From all reports, Yiz spawns 
>in the Northeast corner of the 
>zone, and that's where I found 
>him, hanging near the road into 
>NKarana.  Before you go looking 
>for him, get your "real" character 
>in that area and log out. 
> Log back in as your 
>ranger, and run around for the 
>next 3-4 hours checking to see 
>if he shows up on your 
>tracking list.  When he does, 
>talk to him, and log out. 
> The Splitpaw Assassin that spawns 
>then won't attack you while you 
>camp out.  At least he 
>didn't attack me.  Log back 
>in with your "real" character and 
>kill the Assassin.  Loot the 
>hollowed skull. 
>Now you have some options.  Lynuga, 
>a lvl32 or so caster that 
>hangs out in Innothule Swamp, has 
>the final ruby.  If you 
>have high level (36+)  friends, 
>ask them to kill her.  
>I didn't have any friends that 
>high.  I resorted to running 
>into Guk after I found her 
>and offering 150p to anyone hwo 
>could kill her.  This didn't 
>generate much interest tho.  In 
>the end, I went to one 
>of the weekly bazaars on our 
>server and auctioned that I was 
>interested in lynuga's ruby, and a 
>very nice bard sold me hers 
>for 150p. 
>Best of luck! 
</TEXTAREA>
     
   </TD></TR>
